stimulus:
Study on Face Perception

In this study, you will first be asked to answer questions about yourself, and then rate images of faces them according to certain characteristics.

Your participation in this study is completely voluntary. If you do not wish to complete this survey, simply close your browser.

Your participation in this research will be kept completely confidential. Your responses are anonymous and IP addresses will not be collected to guarantee complete anonymity.

If you have any questions about the project, you may contact the team via the chat option in Prolific.

This project has been reviewed and approved by the University Institutional Review Board (NTU IRB-2022-187).
Questions concerning your rights as a participant in this research may be directed to the NTU-IRB at IRB@ntu.edu.sg or call +65 6592 2495.

Part 1/4

Welcome to the study! Before starting the face perception task, it is important for us to understand our participants' characteristics, so that our conclusions are scientifically valid.

Let's start with some questions about yourself.

Part 2/4

Great! We will continue with a series of questionnaires about your personality.
Again, it is important that you answer truthfully. Please read the statements carefully and answer according to what describe you the best.
Please wait for the experiment to load...

Part 3/4

In this part of the experiment, images of faces will be briefly flashed on the screen.

After each image, you will be asked a series of questions, such as:

  • To what extent do you find this person good-looking (the degree to which the face is aesthetically appealing).

  • How attractive do you find this person (how drawn are you to this person).

  • To what extent do you find this person trustworthy (reliable, honest, responsible etc.,).

  • How much does this person remind you of someone you know (how familiar does this face look to you).


    • Below is an example of how the questions will appear after each image:

We are interested in your first impressions. Please respond according to your gut feelings.
Please wait for the experiment to load...

Part 4/4

In the final part of the experiment, you will see the faces again. Only this time, you have to tell whether they are real or fake.

These images were actually created specially for this experiment: about half of them are photos of real people, and the other half of faces were entirely computer-generated using a new AI algorithm that we want to test.

This algorithm, based on a new generation of deep-learning models, is able to produce photo-realistic images of faces according to pre-specified parameters (e.g., gender, age, emotion, ...).

Among the artificial faces generated, only those that best matched the characteristics of the real photos were selected for this experiment (same background, lighting conditions, age range, etc.).

In order to help us validate our algorithm, we will ask you to tell whether you think the faces you see are real (photos of real people) or fake (computer-generated images).


Please respond according to your gut feelings.

You have come to the end of this study.

Thank you for participating!
